name: NSBundleResourceRequest
desc: A resource manager you use to download content hosted on the App Store at the time your app needs it.

items.name: bundle
items.desc: A reference to the bundle used for storing the downloaded resources. (read-only)

items.name: tags
items.desc: A set of strings, with each string specifying a tag used to mark on-demand resources managed by the request. (read-only)

items.name: endAccessingResources
items.desc: Informs the system that you have finished accessing the resources marked with the tags managed by the request.

items.name: loadingPriority
items.desc: A hint to the system of the relative priority of the resource request.

items.name: progress
items.desc: A reference to the progress object associated with the specified resource request. (read-only)

items.name: NSBundleErrorMaximum
items.desc: The end of the range of error codes reserved for bundle errors.

items.name: NSBundleErrorMinimum
items.desc: The start of the range of error codes reserved for bundle errors.

items.name: NSBundleOnDemandResourceExceededMaximumSizeError
items.desc: The application exceeded the amount of on-demand resources content in use at one time.

items.name: NSBundleOnDemandResourceInvalidTagError
items.desc: The application specified a tag that the system couldnâ€™t find in the application tag manifest.

items.name: NSBundleOnDemandResourceOutOfSpaceError
items.desc: Insufficient space available to download the requested on-demand resources.

items.name: NSBundleResourceRequestLowDiskSpace
items.desc: Posted after the system detects that the amount of available disk space is getting low. The notification is posted to the default notification center.
